<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-30T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-30T16:00:00-05:00" n="42" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d42">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/27</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Vice Consul at Kingston, Jamaica</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BAJ1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bundy</hi></persName>), <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <dateline>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="italic">Kingston</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-30T16:00:00-05:00">
                                <hi rend="italic">July 30, 1914, 4 p.m.</hi>
                            </date>
                            <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 7:35 p.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                        <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                        <p>Jamaica forts manned, regiments hurried to Kingston to-day.<note n="1" xml:id="d42fn1">For further information regarding British military
                                and naval preparations of this date, see the consular despatches
                                from Georgetown (British Guiana), Cardiff, and Cork, which reached
                                the Department on August 14, <hi rend="italic">post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_56">pp. 56</ref>, <ref target="#pg_57">57</ref>,
                                    <ref target="#pg_58">58</ref>.</note> German cruiser <hi rend="italic">Dresden</hi> cruising off three-mile limit. Governor
                            has suppressed all the reports pertaining to military operations.
                            Official report not verified.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_BAJ1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bundy</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>